description: EASY DRAWING HACKS FOR EVERYONEYou don‚Äôt need to be a graduate of art school or have the talent to start drawing. Moreover, have you ever noticed that it‚Äôs really hard to draw eyes without knowing basic techniques? We share an easy way to draw eyes: draw an almond shape, add shading around the eye and add eyeliner. Draw eyelashes and remember that they should have a different length. Shade inner corners of the eye and enhance the realism effect by adding shades and make it look sparkly. Watch our easy tutorial!The next creative idea is to make a bleach pen! Firstly, you need to pour bleach into the bowl. Next, remove the tip out of a highlighter and soak it until the original color is gone. Usually, it takes a couple of hours. After that, you can start creating! For example, you can cover the canvas with any paint you want and make a print using a bleach pen. title: Bright n small color rangoli designs for Sankranthi/Pongal || latest easy festival muggulu 2019
tags: rangoli,rangoli designs,kolam,kolam designs,muggulu,muggulu designs,rangoli with dots,rangoli designs with dots,easy rangoli,easy rangoli designs,rangoli art,rangoli art designs,rangoli kolam,kolam rangoli,kolam with dots,kolam designs with dots,simple kolam,padi kolam,easy kolam,muggulu with dots,muggulu designs with dots,chukkala muggulu,designs,designs with dots,how to draw,latest rangoli,indian art,indian rangoli,Sankranthi/Pongal kolam
description: It is our tradition to draw kolam every day morning at the door steps.There are many benifits of drawing kolam in front of the house.It is auspecious and believes Godess Lakshmi enters the house if kolam is drawn.Kolam brings lot of positive vibrations and energy to you and your home.Draw kolam soon after you wake up and then do your prayers.Kolam or rangoli is a part of Indian culture and transferred from generation to next generation.This ancient art form is also called as muggulu in parts  of South India like Andhra pradesh and Telangana.People draw different creative rangoli kolam designs using kolam powder or muggu pindi which is actually crushed Lime stone powder available at different parts of India.There are different types of rangoli or kolam designs like dots kolam, sikku kolam, padi kolam, Margazhi kolam.People draw special rangoli designs for Festivals like Sankranthi (Pongal), Diwali (Deepavali), Vijaya dasami (Dasara).Women create deepam rangoli or kolam designs during diwali festival time, create very big and Dhanurmasam muggulu (Margazhi) for Sankranthi or Pongal festival.It is a belief among the people that drawing muggulu infront of the house in the early morning soon after wake bringsgood fortune to them and their family.People mix rice flour to lime stone powder and prepare their own kolam powder. Muggulu can also be drawn with rice flour only.These Beautiful and creative designs are decorated with flowers based on the occasion or festival.

This is Pune, Maharashtra special recipe. Different spices are stuffed, rolled and fried. These taste just awesome. You just can‚Äôt stop yourself from eating more. Do try this recipe at home and drop a comment for me. Do not forget to like, share and subscribe.Ingredients:‚Ä¢ 1 cup Maida‚Ä¢ 1 tbsp Besan‚Ä¢ Salt to taste‚Ä¢ 1/4 tsp Ajwain / Carom seeds‚Ä¢ 2 tbsp smoking hot Oil‚Ä¢ Water‚Ä¢ 1 tbsp Coriander seeds‚Ä¢ 1/2 tsp fennel seeds‚Ä¢ 1/2 tsp Cumin seeds‚Ä¢ 1 tbsp Sesame seeds‚Ä¢ 1/2 tbsp Poppy seeds‚Ä¢  1/2 cup dry shredded Coconut‚Ä¢ 1 tsp Red chili powder‚Ä¢ 1/2 tsp Garam masala‚Ä¢ Salt to taste‚Ä¢ 1/2 tsp Sugar‚Ä¢ Tamarind-Gudh chutney‚Ä¢ Shev‚Ä¢ Oil for fryingMethod:‚Ä¢ Take maida in a dish. ‚Ä¢ Add besam, salt, ajwain and mix well. ‚Ä¢ Always crush ajiwain between your palms while adding so that it   releases nice flavour. ‚Ä¢ Mix everything well together. ‚Ä¢ Add hot oil and mix well. ‚Ä¢ When the oil cools down a little rub it well to all the maida. ‚Ä¢ Add a little water at a time and knead stiff dough. ‚Ä¢ The dough should be soft at all. ‚Ä¢ Transfer the dough into a bowl, cover and rest it for just about 10   minutes. ‚Ä¢ Heat up a pan on medium heat. ‚Ä¢ Add coriander seeds, fennel seeds, cumin seeds and roast   everything for just about a minute. Do not roast longer. ‚Ä¢ After about a minute or so add sesame seeds, poppy seeds and   roast everything for about 30-40 seconds. ‚Ä¢ Add dry coconut and roast until it gets light golden color. ‚Ä¢ Transfer the roasted spices into a bender jar and add red chili   powder, garam masala, salt to taste, sugar when these cool down   a little. ‚Ä¢ Blend everything into fine powder and masala for bakarwadi is   already. ‚Ä¢ Take the dough and divide it into 3 equal portions. ‚Ä¢ Make each portion nice and smooth. ‚Ä¢ Roll a portion into a little thin round disc. ‚Ä¢ The chapatti should be thin at the center and a little thick at the   eges. ‚Ä¢ The chapatti should not be too thin. ‚Ä¢ Spread tamarind gudh chutney on the chapatti. ‚Ä¢ Add the masala on the chutney and spread it well. ‚Ä¢ Spread some shev on the masala. Leave some gap along the   edges. ‚Ä¢ Roll the masala on the chapatti with rolling pin once. ‚Ä¢ Lift one edge and make tight roll. ‚Ä¢ Cut the edges off and cut the roll into about 1‚Äù vadi. ‚Ä¢ Press each vadi a little so that masala won‚Äôt come out while   frying. ‚Ä¢ Do not press much. The vadi should retain its shape. ‚Ä¢ Heat up oil on low heat. ‚Ä¢ Drop the vadi into hot oil and fry it on low heat only for about 5-6   minutes. ‚Ä¢ Keep on stirring with a fork at the intervals. ‚Ä¢ When the vadi is fried well from on sides, take them out. ‚Ä¢ Bakarwadi is already. description: Romeo Weds Heer - Episode 14 | HAR PAL GEOAfter giving us the blockbuster drama serial Khaani, ace producers Abdullah Kadwani and Asad Qureshi are bringing the favorite couple Feroz Khan and Sana Javed back, in the 7th Sky Entertainment‚Äôs mega project, Romeo Weds Heer. Directed by the renowned director Anjum Shehzad who is known for his commendable work in Khaani and written by legendary writer Muhammad Younis Butt who has penned the famous satirical show Hum Sab Umeed Se Hain, Romeo Weds Heer is a romantic comedy that is for the masses.7th Sky Entertainment presents Feroz Khan and Sana Javed in a complete new avatar. The first look of the serial unveiled by Geo Entertainment features the title track of Romeo Weds Heer, sung by the renowned singers Aima Baig and Sahir Ali Bhagga, and the colorful music video for the track has been choreographed by Wahab Shah.  The track is full of fun and entertainment and the screen chemistry of Feroz & Sana in the dance number is amazing. The dance number of Romeo Weds Heer has made the audience glued to the screen. Romeo Weds Heer is scheduled to go on air in October 2018 on Geo TV.A love story for generations to come in a serial redefining love, where east meets west. In our society marriage is not just between two individuals but between two families and when these families are poles apart this will bring twist and turns in Romeo and Heer‚Äôs life.So fasten your seatbelts belts & get ready for the fun & excitement in a signature Rom-com to celebrate the true colors of love & happiness in the one & only love story of the year.Written by: Dr. Muhammad Younis ButtDirected by: Anjum ShahzadProduced by: Abdullah Kadwani & Asad QureshiProduction House: 7th Sky EntertainmentFor More Videos Subscribe - https://www.youtube.com/harpalgeoFor More Videos Subscribe - https://www.youtube.com/harpalgeo#RomeoWedsHeer#HARPALGEO#GEO#FerozKhan#Sanajaved
